These are Puzzles for 2x6 Level 8

.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-8-1::.
The people use 6 different means of transport: skateboard, airplane, ship, bike, van, scooter
6 different games are played: monopoly, whist, chess, canasta, backgammon, billiard
 1. the person playing chess is on the left of the person driving the skateboard##1
 2. the person driving the airplane is on the left or right of the person playing whist##3
 3. the person driving the airplane is somewhere to the right of the person playing monopoly##5
 4. the person playing billiard is not to the left of the person driving the ship##8
 5. the person driving the scooter is somewhere to the right of the person playing backgammon##5
 6. the person playing backgammon is somewhere between the person playing chess and the person driving the scooter##7
 7. the person driving the skateboard is not to the left of the person playing chess##8
 8. the person driving the van is on the left or right of the person playing whist##3
 9. the person driving the scooter is on the left or right of the person driving the van##3
10. the person playing monopoly is not to the left of the person driving the bike##8
11. the person playing backgammon is somewhere to the right of the person driving the bike##5
12. the person driving the airplane is on the right of the person driving the bike##1
13. the person driving the ship is somewhere to the right of the person playing chess##5
14. the person driving the scooter is somewhere between the person playing whist and the person driving the ship##7
15. the person playing billiard is somewhere to the right of the person playing monopoly##5
16. the person driving the van is not the person playing canasta##6

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1     |    2    |   3    |   4   |       5        |   6   |
| Transport           | bike | airplane | skateboard | van | scooter | ship |
| Game   | monopoly | chess    | whist  | backgammon  | canasta            | billiard  |

