.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-8-3::.
There are 6 different favourite colors: turquise, azure, purple, pink, green, ebony
6 different games are played: snooker, monopoly, go, bridge, scrabble, chess
 1. the person playing monopoly is somewhere to the left of the person who likes purple##5
 2. the person who likes azure is somewhere to the right of the person playing monopoly##5
 3. the person playing chess is somewhere to the right of the person who likes green##5
 4. the person playing go is not to the left of the person who likes azure##8
 5. the person who likes purple is somewhere to the left of the person playing chess##5
 6. the person who likes ebony is on the left or right of the person who likes purple##3
 7. the person playing snooker is somewhere to the right of the person who likes purple##5
 8. the person who likes pink is not to the right of the person who likes pink##8
 9. the person who likes turquise is somewhere to the right of the person who likes purple##5
10. the person playing bridge is on the far right##1
11. the person playing chess is somewhere between the person who likes green and the person playing go##7
12. the person playing monopoly is somewhere to the left of the person playing go##5
13. the person who likes ebony is between the person playing scrabble and the person playing chess##2
14. the person who likes azure is on the right of the person who likes pink##1
15. the person playing go is somewhere between the person playing chess and the person who likes turquise##7
16. the person playing scrabble is not to the left of the person playing scrabble##8
17. the person playing chess is somewhere to the right of the person playing scrabble##5
18. the person who likes green is the person playing monopoly##1
19. the person playing go is not the person who likes turquise##6

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1     |    2    |     3      |       4       |     5     |    6     |
| Color   | green   | purple | ebony    | pink      | azure | turquise |
| Game         | monopoly | scrabble  | snooker | chess | go   | bridge  |

